TITLE: Critics rip DeSantis for Trump comment they say makes him sound like 'Crooked Hillary'
SUMMARY: Republican presidential candidate Gov. Ron DeSantis sparked an uproar over the weekend for comments he made about former President Donald Trump's base.

TITLE: Ramaswamy changes tune from previous comments on Trump ahead of GOP debate: ‘Not the same Donald Trump’
SUMMARY: Republican presidential candidate Vivek Ramaswamy said he’s "fine" with former President Donald Trump not showing up at the first debate despite singing a different tune in May.

TITLE: White House hopeful optimistic Trump will make last-minute decision to join first GOP debate
SUMMARY: Former Vice President Mike Pence said he hopes former President Donald Trump will make a last-minute announcement and join the first Republican primary presidential debate.

TITLE: Racing against the clock: GOP presidential long shots work furiously to qualify for first Republican debate
SUMMARY: Roughly half a dozen Republican White House contenders are desperately trying to make the stage for Wednesday’s Fox News-hosted first GOP presidential nomination debate.

TITLE: Biden FEMA chief warns of disaster relief funding shortage after Maui fires, as California braces for storm
SUMMARY: FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell said disaster relief funding could have a shortage by mid-September after Hawaii's wildfires and California's storm.

TITLE: Biden quietly auctions off border wall parts to stunt Republican effort to restart construction: report
SUMMARY: The Biden Department of Defense is reportedly selling off excess border wall materials after the Republican-sponsored FINISH IT Act cleared the Senate.

TITLE: Hunter Biden’s defense lawyers vowed to put President Biden on the stand
SUMMARY: Hunter Biden's attorney said he would have President Biden take the stand in defense of his son if the Justice Department brought charges against Hunter.

TITLE: DC continues experiencing soaring crime rates despite council chairman saying 'there is no crime crisis'
SUMMARY: Democratic D.C. Council Chairman Phil Mendelson said earlier this year there is no crime crisis in the nation's capital. Meanwhile, crime has skyrocketed.

TITLE: First GOP presidential debate is 'enormously important' as candidates seek ‘breakout moments’
SUMMARY: In a Republican presidential nomination race dominated by former President Donald Trump, the Fox News-hosted first debate offers other candidates a breakout moment opportunity.

TITLE: Georgia Judge blocks provision prohibiting the distribution of water at voting polls
SUMMARY: A federal judge temporarily blocked a provision in Georgia's voting law prohibiting people from giving food and water to voters waiting in line to vote.

TITLE: Jimmy Carter and wife are in 'final chapter' of lives, grandson says
SUMMARY: Jimmy Carter's grandson says his grandparents are in the "final chapter" of their lives, according to an interview with PEOPLE published on Saturday.

TITLE: Texas Democratic county official announces switch to the GOP, cites border policies: 'An unprecedented crisis'
SUMMARY: Texas Democrat Kira Talip Sanchez, who serves as Kleberg County Attorney, announced her switch to the Republican Party on Saturday, citing border security policy as a main reason.

TITLE: DeSantis opens up about leaked debate strategy memo, vows to punch back in first GOP showdown
SUMMARY: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis says he's 'ready to do what we need to' at Wednesday's Fox News-hosted first Republican presidential nomination debate

TITLE: DeSantis offers to assist California with Hurricane Hilary 'in any way we can'
SUMMARY: Florida's Governor Ron DeSantis has offered to assist California "any way we can" with Hurricane Hilary preparation and relief efforts, citing Florida's vast experience with hurricanes.

TITLE: Migrant encounters at southern border on the rise again after Biden touted immigration policy reforms
SUMMARY: Official border statistics released on Friday show a new increase in migrant encounters at the southern border in July, with numbers exceeding 180,000.

TITLE: DeSantis meets with Kemp amid Trump case, impeachment calls against Fani Willis
SUMMARY: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis spoke with Gov. Brian Kemp on Friday in Buckshead, Georgia, in a private meeting.

TITLE: California GOP proposal would distance state party from national messaging on abortion, same-sex marriage
SUMMARY: Republicans in California are seeking to remove certain messaging related to abortion and same-sex marriage from the state party's platform.

TITLE: Former Attorney General Alberto Gonzales says Trump 'should serve time' if found guilty in Jan. 6 case
SUMMARY: Former U.S. Attorney General Alberto Gonzales said on MSNBC that former President Donald Trump "should serve time" if convicted in his 2020 election case.

TITLE: What’s next for the one-time red state turned southwestern battleground?
SUMMARY: Arizona was a reliably red state for decades, but Democrats have enjoyed success in statewide contests the past three election cycles. The state is now a key battleground

TITLE: James Buckley, conservative former US senator from New York, dead at 100
SUMMARY: James Buckley, a former U.S. senator from New York and a former judge on the U.S. Appeals Court for Washington D.C., died Friday at the age of 100.

TITLE: Maui company says request for water to fight wildfire delayed several hours while state consulted with farmers
SUMMARY: A Maui company says that efforts to divert water to fight the recent devastating wildfire were delayed because a government official said he had to check with local farmers.

TITLE: Gun industry cries foul after hundreds of gun dealers lose licenses amid Biden administration crackdown
SUMMARY: An uptick in the amount of gun dealers who have had their licenses revoked by the Biden administration has some in the industry suggesting they are being targeted.

TITLE: House Dem shreds 'radical leftist elites,' defends voting down Biden student loan handout
SUMMARY: Democratic Rep. Jared Golden unloaded on left-wing "elitists" amid scrutiny over his moderate liberal group getting a donation from a student loan provider.

TITLE: Obama-Biden admin defended use of 'alternate email addresses' long before Biden's aliases were revealed
SUMMARY: The Obama-Biden White House said in 2013 it believed using “alternate email addresses" for high-ranking officials made “eminent sense."

TITLE: Pence preps for showdown with Trump at first Republican debate —  even if Trump doesn't show up
SUMMARY: Mike Pence appears ready to face off with former President Donald Trump at next week’s first Republican presidential nomination debate, even if his former running mate is not on stage
